  "prompt": "What is the average electric bill for a 2-bedroom apartment in the Bay Area?",
  "response": "The average electric bill for a 2-bedroom apartment in the Bay Area can vary widely depending on factors such as usage patterns, energy efficiency, time of year, and the specific utility provider. However, as of recent data, the average monthly electric bill for a 2-bedroom apartment in the Bay Area typically ranges from **$50 to $150**.\n\n### Key Factors Influencing the Bill:\n1. **Seasonal Changes**: Bills tend to be higher in summer due to air conditioning and in winter due to heating.\n2. **Energy Efficiency**: Apartments with energy-efficient appliances and good insulation may have lower bills.\n3. **Usage Habits**: Usage of high-consumption appliances (e.g., laundry machines, dishwashers) can increase costs.\n4. **Utility Rates**: Pacific Gas & Electric (PG&E), the primary utility provider in the Bay Area, has relatively high rates compared to other regions in the U.S.\n\n### Tips to Lower Your Bill:\n- Use LED bulbs and energy-efficient appliances.\n- Adjust thermostats to reduce heating and cooling usage.\n- Take advantage of PG&E\u2019s time-of-use plans to save money during off-peak hours.\n\nFor a more accurate estimate, check your specific usage on your utility bill or use PG&E\u2019s online tools to analyze your consumption.",
